## Dependencies

No `requirements.txt` is provided.

If you want to run this project, you’ll need to create your own virtual environment and install the required Python packages yourself.

### Quick setup
```bash
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

Install dependencies manually
Install what the code imports (common ones used here include flask, requests, pandas, numpy, scikit-learn, scipy, etc.). Example:
pip install flask requests pandas numpy scikit-learn scipy etc.. 

If something errors with ModuleNotFoundError, install that module via pip install <module>.

If you want it even more blunt (matching the vibe):
```md
